WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.867
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:01.867 --> 00:00:04.434
Praise the Lord and welcome to our broadcast.

00:00:04.434 --> 00:00:07.546
Well, it's Diana and Brandon and we're excited to be here.

00:00:07.546 --> 00:00:08.817
We have some things on our heart.

00:00:09.075 --> 00:00:12.297
There's a lot going on, and I say that every time.

00:00:12.297 --> 00:00:18.040
But my goodness, we laugh about it because of all the things that are happening right now.

00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:22.629
It seems like every time you turn around, there's something new going on.

00:00:22.629 --> 00:00:28.480
I mean, the IRS is getting rid of 20,000 people.

00:00:29.794 --> 00:00:33.360
Then we had the main IRS guy say he's quitting.

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:35.280
That's a big deal in America.

00:00:35.280 --> 00:00:45.582
I don't know, that might not be a big deal to other nations right now because I know I'm talking to everybody, but here, it's like a circus on the news.

00:00:45.582 --> 00:00:47.150
What is going on?

00:00:53.380 --> 00:00:53.650
The stock market is still kind of teeter-tottery, but God's still on the throne.

00:00:54.420 --> 00:00:57.093
He's not falling off and the sky is not falling.

00:00:57.093 --> 00:01:01.359
All we know is that Jesus is coming and he's coming soon.

00:01:01.359 --> 00:01:04.194
But I have a word of encouragement for y'all today.

00:01:04.651 --> 00:01:09.982
One of my favorite passages in the Bible is Genesis 26.

00:01:09.982 --> 00:01:12.516
There was famine in the land.

00:01:12.516 --> 00:01:28.479
And I know that God told me—I feel in my spirit—'Brandon, I'm going to give you a window of opportunity before a major shaking takes place, a major opportunity for the body of Christ, the ones that are listening.

00:01:28.479 --> 00:01:30.102
' And I'm praying for that opportunity.

00:01:30.102 --> 00:01:37.467
Show us, Lord, what it is for the windows to open up over our household because I know what he's called us to do.

00:01:37.467 --> 00:01:41.520
And we cannot do it in the natural without a surplus.

00:01:41.520 --> 00:01:48.160
It's going to take the fishes and the loaves type of a miracle for what God has called Diana and I to do in these last days.

00:01:48.640 --> 00:01:50.600
We talk about it and we pray about it.

00:01:50.600 --> 00:01:57.147
I know we haven't stepped fully into what he's told us to do, but you don't start at a run.

00:01:57.147 --> 00:02:01.017
You start to learn how to walk and jog first, right?

00:02:01.451 --> 00:02:03.472
Most people try to run first.

00:02:04.624 --> 00:02:06.820
It's time to apply some wisdom with this.

00:02:06.820 --> 00:02:17.946
But I was thinking about the passage where there was famine in the land with Isaac, and he planted and he sowed in famine.

00:02:18.319 --> 00:02:19.400
Just read that, honey.

00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:21.530
I think it's just a blessing.

00:02:21.880 --> 00:02:28.452
You can read the first couple of verses up here and then let's go down to verse 12.

00:02:28.452 --> 00:02:35.280
'And there was a famine in the land other than the former famine that was in the days of Abraham.

00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:44.233
And Isaac went to Gerar to Abimelech, king—I probably butchered that—Abimelech, king of the Philistines.

00:02:44.233 --> 00:02:48.879
And the Lord appeared to him and said, "Do not go down to Egypt.

00:02:48.879 --> 00:02:58.708
Live in the land of which I will tell you, dwell temporarily in this land, and I will be with you and will favor you with blessings for you and to your descendants.

00:02:58.708 --> 00:03:06.600
I will give all these lands and I will perform the oath which I swore to Abraham your father and I will make your descendants...

00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:09.440
"' So pause right there for a second.

00:03:09.440 --> 00:03:12.187
A key to walking in the blessing is obedience.

00:03:12.693 --> 00:03:18.709
Just right there: being where God has called you to be regardless of what you feel.

00:03:18.709 --> 00:03:22.280
Don't go down to Egypt because that's probably where the hot spot was.

00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:25.303
It's probably the major hub of all the finances back then.

00:03:25.577 --> 00:03:28.239
Egypt was probably it, I'm sure.

00:03:28.788 --> 00:03:32.262
So everybody was like, 'We got to go to Egypt because that's where the money's at.

00:03:32.262 --> 00:03:34.068
' But he says, 'Stay where you are.

00:03:34.068 --> 00:03:35.1000
' And there's a famine in the land.

00:03:35.1000 --> 00:03:38.171
I'm sure Isaac was like, 'What?

00:03:38.171 --> 00:03:38.549
Seriously?

00:03:38.549 --> 00:03:46.285
' So he went down to the king Abimelech to the Philistines because he's like, 'We got to go try to make some trade deals or something.

00:03:46.285 --> 00:03:51.031
' But going all the way down—because this is a big chapter—read verse 12.

00:03:55.348 --> 00:03:57.006
That's my favorite.

00:03:57.006 --> 00:04:04.560
'Then Isaac sowed seed in that land and received in the same year a hundred times as much as he had planted.

00:04:04.560 --> 00:04:08.400
And the Lord favored him with blessings.

00:04:08.400 --> 00:04:12.607
' I just thought if God did it for him, he'll do it every single time.

00:04:13.615 --> 00:04:15.892
But he had to do something.

00:04:15.892 --> 00:04:17.759
He had to sow the seed.

00:04:17.759 --> 00:04:25.600
He didn't just sit back and wait for God to do it; he didn't just say, 'God, make it happen.

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:27.484
' He sowed the seed.

00:04:29.369 --> 00:04:31.783
And just like we do, we sow into the offerings.

00:04:31.783 --> 00:04:33.497
We sow into the church.

00:04:33.497 --> 00:04:35.520
We sow into God's work.

00:04:35.939 --> 00:04:43.787
In that sowing into what God has called you to do by being obedient to the word whenever he tells you to do it, he obeyed him.

00:04:43.787 --> 00:04:47.140
He sowed and he stayed in the land where he was supposed to be.

00:04:47.140 --> 00:04:53.120
And he sowed in famine whenever we see what's going on on the news right now.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:54.629
The sky is falling, Chicken Little.

00:04:54.629 --> 00:04:57.680
I mean, it's like trade wars.

00:04:57.680 --> 00:05:02.834
Oh no, China's done something else—stopping the minerals and the magnets.

00:05:03.451 --> 00:05:07.771
My goodness, it looks like a famine's trying to come on.

00:05:07.771 --> 00:05:14.080
It looks like what I hear is that Warren Buffett has all this and what they're doing.

00:05:14.320 --> 00:05:19.940
I get all these articles and it causes your flesh to shake a little bit.

00:05:19.940 --> 00:05:30.560
Like I told you, if you're going horizontal, looking at everything right now in the natural, it makes you go, 'Whoa, a little shaky.

00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:32.920
' I'm like, 'Hold on a minute.

00:05:32.920 --> 00:05:36.670
' For what the Lord has blessed us with, you go, 'Should we bury it?

00:05:36.670 --> 00:05:38.429
' You start thinking in the natural.

00:05:45.783 --> 00:05:52.800
But you have to think in the spiritual because I'm going to tell you: sowing in famine sounds really dumb.

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:57.093
Why would you sow any seed when there's no rain?

00:05:57.093 --> 00:05:59.919
There's drought; it's famine.

00:05:59.919 --> 00:06:01.680
But he obeyed God.

00:06:01.680 --> 00:06:04.263
He sowed in famine and he reaped.

00:06:04.263 --> 00:06:05.086
Read it again.

00:06:05.086 --> 00:06:05.806
What happened?

00:06:05.806 --> 00:06:13.520
'Then Isaac sowed seed in that land and received in the same year a hundred times as much as he had planted.

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:15.600
And the Lord favored him with blessings.

00:06:15.600 --> 00:06:21.216
And the man became great and gained more and more until he became very wealthy and distinguished.

00:06:21.216 --> 00:06:26.560
He owned flocks, herds, and a great supply of servants.

00:06:26.560 --> 00:06:28.789
And the Philistines envied him.

00:06:28.789 --> 00:06:34.479
' Now, why would they envy him?

00:06:34.479 --> 00:06:36.960
Because it didn't happen to the unjust.

00:06:36.960 --> 00:06:43.227
They were jealous because their crops didn't turn around and reap a hundredfold.

00:06:43.227 --> 00:06:44.507
They were going, 'What gives?

00:06:44.507 --> 00:06:48.959
' and looking at him going, 'He's walking in the blessing and the favor of God's all over him.

00:06:48.959 --> 00:06:53.302
' And he's doing exactly what God had called him to do in the famine.

00:06:53.685 --> 00:06:58.685
The blessing and the favor of the Lord was on him in a supernatural way.

00:06:58.685 --> 00:07:06.560
Now, ladies and gentlemen, if God would do that for Isaac in famine, how much more will he do it for you?

00:07:06.560 --> 00:07:14.594
How much more will God bless your hands and whatever you put your hands to will it prosper if you just believe him?

00:07:14.594 --> 00:07:23.199
If you put your boat into motion and not sit idly by and go, 'Well, where's my angel with the money sack?

00:07:23.199 --> 00:07:24.891
' Isaac planted in famine.

00:07:24.891 --> 00:07:29.488
But you have to be—bottom line—you have to be where God has called you to be.

00:07:29.488 --> 00:07:32.364
You have to be doing what God has called you to do.

00:07:32.364 --> 00:07:37.520
And if you are and you're in that place of obedience, blessing is behind the obedience.

00:07:37.520 --> 00:07:42.160
So keep going, baby.

00:07:42.160 --> 00:07:44.080
You can keep reading.

00:07:44.080 --> 00:07:52.479
'Now all the wells which his father's servants had dug in the days of Abraham his father, the Philistines had closed and filled with earth.

00:07:52.479 --> 00:07:54.199
' And that's jealousy right there.

00:07:54.532 --> 00:07:56.279
They're going to fill all those wells up.

00:07:56.279 --> 00:07:58.620
'We don't want you blessed, so we're going to fill your well up.

00:07:58.620 --> 00:08:07.714
' There's always going to be somebody trying to fill your well up, trying to put dirt on your well coming out of you.

00:08:07.714 --> 00:08:08.720
'Oh, that can't happen.

00:08:08.720 --> 00:08:09.999
You'll never make it.

00:08:09.999 --> 00:08:12.479
' Those are the well cover-uppers here.

00:08:12.479 --> 00:08:22.755
We don't have actual wells that they try to block, but there's always somebody trying to speak doubt into your faith, telling you you can't do what God's told you you can do.

00:08:22.755 --> 00:08:25.796
And don't you know there's famine out there, dummy?

00:08:26.982 --> 00:08:30.239
But you have your eyes on God.

00:08:30.239 --> 00:08:31.199
You're going vertical.

00:08:33.216 --> 00:08:34.959
They filled the wells up.

00:08:34.959 --> 00:08:38.743
Sorry for interjecting what the Lord said.

00:08:38.743 --> 00:08:45.062
Abimelech said to Isaac, 'Go away from us, for you are much mightier than we are.

00:08:45.062 --> 00:08:50.399
' So Isaac went away from there and pitched his tent in the valley of Gerar and dwelt there.

00:08:50.399 --> 00:08:58.119
And Isaac dug again the wells of water which had been dug in the days of Abraham his father, for the Philistines had stopped them after the death of Abraham.

00:08:58.119 --> 00:09:01.794
And he gave them the names by which his father had called them.

00:09:01.794 --> 00:09:05.947
Now Isaac's servants dug in the valley and found there a well of living spring water.

00:09:06.746 --> 00:09:13.480
And the herdsmen of Gerar quarreled with Isaac's herdsmen, saying, 'The water is ours.

00:09:13.480 --> 00:09:18.125
' And he named the well Esek, meaning contention, because they quarreled with him.

00:09:18.125 --> 00:09:21.610
Then his servants dug another well and they quarreled over that also.

00:09:21.610 --> 00:09:24.777
So he named it Sitnah, meaning enmity.

00:09:24.777 --> 00:09:30.503
And he moved away from there and dug another well; for that one they did not quarrel.

00:09:30.503 --> 00:09:39.120
He named it Rehoboth, meaning room, saying, 'For now the Lord has made room for us and we will be fruitful in the land.

00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:43.234
' Yeah, but there are always going to be people trying to leech off your blessing too.

00:09:43.234 --> 00:09:46.720
But there's so much abundance on you that it won't matter.

00:09:46.720 --> 00:09:54.640
Now he went up from there to Beersheba, and the Lord appeared to him that same night and said, 'I am the God of Abraham your father.

00:09:54.640 --> 00:10:02.800
Fear not, for I am with you, and I will favor you with blessings and multiply your descendants for the sake of my servant Abraham.

00:10:02.800 --> 00:10:07.253
' And Isaac built an altar there and called on the name of the Lord and pitched his tent there.

00:10:07.253 --> 00:10:10.577
And there Isaac's servants were digging a well.

00:10:10.577 --> 00:10:12.924
Basically, a well is life.

00:10:12.924 --> 00:10:19.840
Even in our time right now, a well brings forth life; it brings forth greenery.

00:10:20.160 --> 00:10:25.396
Because if you don't have the fresh living water of the word coming up out of you, you're dry.

00:10:25.396 --> 00:10:27.911
So even then, it's a type and shadow.

00:10:27.911 --> 00:10:36.606
We've got to get in that river, that well coming up out of us, and have that going on in these last days in the time of famine.

00:10:36.606 --> 00:10:38.576
There's a word famine going on too.

00:10:38.576 --> 00:10:43.520
If you haven't noticed, there seems to be a word famine.

00:10:43.520 --> 00:10:56.249
And we see that Isaac was determined to keep the wells open because he knew where the life came from.

00:10:56.249 --> 00:10:59.260
He knew how much he had to have that living well.

00:10:59.260 --> 00:11:07.200
How much more do we need that living well coming up out of us and having this freshness of this new fire?

00:11:08.446 --> 00:11:10.906
It sounds like the Lord himself appeared.

00:11:10.906 --> 00:11:16.229
It says the Lord appeared to him in the Old Covenant, y'all.

00:11:17.623 --> 00:11:18.960
This isn't New Covenant.

00:11:19.600 --> 00:11:26.149
How many of y'all know that Jesus will appear to you and will have a relationship with you?

00:11:26.149 --> 00:11:29.211
But you think, 'Well, it's just for Brandon; it's just for Diana.

00:11:29.211 --> 00:11:32.555
The Lord just appears to them; He won't talk to me.

00:11:32.555 --> 00:11:35.440
' He's no respecter of persons.

00:11:35.440 --> 00:11:48.187
And I want to tell you all, from what I have seen coming, you better get Genesis 26 down inside of you, understanding that we can sow in famine.

00:11:48.187 --> 00:11:56.730
And not only can we sow in famine, but we can reap a hundredfold that same year because God is with us.

00:11:56.730 --> 00:11:58.492
Is God with you?

00:11:58.492 --> 00:12:04.490
I'm going to say it: God is with me, and He is with Diana, and He is with Braden, and He is with my daughters.

00:12:04.490 --> 00:12:05.784
He is with us.

00:12:05.784 --> 00:12:10.040
If God is for me, who can be against me?

00:12:10.040 --> 00:12:20.880
If goodness and mercy are chasing me down—the Bible says, 'Then goodness and mercy will follow me all the days of my life and I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

00:12:20.880 --> 00:12:31.139
' If goodness and mercy are following us and the blessing of the Lord is following you—from what I have seen coming, we have a window, and I'm still praying over that window.

00:12:31.139 --> 00:12:34.515
I am like, 'Devil, you aren't holding back my blessing.

00:12:34.515 --> 00:12:39.644
Let go of my money that God has called for us to have.

00:12:39.644 --> 00:12:44.160
' And you get the Holy Ghost; He gives us creative ideas to do it.

00:12:44.160 --> 00:12:48.206
And whatever He tells you to do, like I said before, do it.

00:12:48.206 --> 00:12:52.176
Like Mary, who said, 'Whatever He tells you to do, do it.

00:12:52.176 --> 00:12:53.620
Fill up the pots with water.

00:12:53.620 --> 00:13:01.200
' Look at Elijah telling the widow, 'Make me a piece of cake with the last grain that you have and prepare it for me.

00:13:01.200 --> 00:13:02.159
' And guess what happened?

00:13:02.159 --> 00:13:04.784
She did it, but it was the last of what she had.

00:13:04.784 --> 00:13:09.040
And then he told her to go get all the pots that she could find.

00:13:11.600 --> 00:13:11.920
Why?

00:13:11.920 --> 00:13:16.575
Because you sowed in famine.

00:13:16.575 --> 00:13:18.395
And now guess what?

00:13:18.395 --> 00:13:21.405
Get ready to reap your hundredfold return.

00:13:21.405 --> 00:13:29.720
And all the pots she could find filled up with oil, so much so that she had enough to pay the debt.

00:13:29.720 --> 00:13:32.345
She had enough to do everything she needed to do.

00:13:32.345 --> 00:13:33.618
She had a surplus.

00:13:33.618 --> 00:13:37.214
Do you know we serve a God of the surplus?

00:13:37.214 --> 00:13:40.299
We serve a God of the running over.

00:13:40.299 --> 00:13:43.519
We serve a God of the overflow.

00:13:43.519 --> 00:13:45.680
He's not just a 'barely getting by' God.

00:13:45.680 --> 00:13:47.929
He's a hundredfold return God.

00:13:48.829 --> 00:13:52.480
You sow in famine when it doesn't make any sense to sow it.

00:13:52.480 --> 00:14:05.550
And you've got the Philistines and you've got Wall Street and you've got whoever they are around you looking at you and going, 'How in the world is he thriving in an economy like this?

00:14:05.550 --> 00:14:10.000
How is he thriving in an economy like what's going to come?

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:11.840
' From what I told you, like the 1930s.

00:14:11.840 --> 00:14:13.633
You say, 'Well, can we stop that?

00:14:13.633 --> 00:14:13.988
' No.

00:14:13.988 --> 00:14:16.300
There are going to be dark, dark days.

00:14:16.300 --> 00:14:17.380
I've told you this.

00:14:17.380 --> 00:14:19.566
The horses are riding.

00:14:19.566 --> 00:14:22.400
And most people go, 'When is that happening?

00:14:22.400 --> 00:14:23.440
' Just look around you.

00:14:23.440 --> 00:14:23.840
Who knows?

00:14:23.840 --> 00:14:30.110
But I'm going to tell you, I'm always going to have my eyes fixed on Him, listening to Him, not worried about when, when, when.

00:14:31.035 --> 00:14:33.519
I don't need to worry about when.

00:14:33.519 --> 00:14:36.685
All I need to do is keep staying vertical and listening to Him.

00:14:36.685 --> 00:14:39.662
And He will tell me when to plant the seed.

00:14:39.662 --> 00:14:42.057
He will tell me when to give.

00:14:42.057 --> 00:14:47.859
He's not going to let me sit by and go, 'Well, you didn't give it a couple of weeks ago when I told you to, so you're going to starve.

00:14:47.859 --> 00:14:50.844
' That's not the kind of God we serve.

00:14:50.844 --> 00:15:05.464
If He takes care of the lilies of the field and He takes care of the sparrows of the air, how much more—if He took care of the widow with the son and the debts and all the things that He's done in the past?

00:15:05.464 --> 00:15:11.200
They honored the man of God and they did what he said to do more than one time.

00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:14.503
And then we see Isaac having a blessing like this.

00:15:14.503 --> 00:15:19.920
You see all these beautiful testimonies in this beautiful book that God's given us.

00:15:19.920 --> 00:15:25.724
And I just wanted to encourage you all today with all the things that are going on right now.

00:15:25.724 --> 00:15:30.160
And they say it's a new economy and they're trying to do all this new stuff.

00:15:30.160 --> 00:15:36.097
All I want you to know is that it might get darker before it gets light.

00:15:36.097 --> 00:15:43.666
But I know that if we're in that place of famine, He'll do the same for us.

00:15:43.666 --> 00:15:50.639
It may all be a complete meltdown of the economy in the days ahead.

00:15:50.639 --> 00:15:51.439
Might be.

00:15:51.439 --> 00:16:01.897
But if Isaac can sow in famine and reap a hundredfold that same year, how much more is our God able to do it for us?

00:16:01.897 --> 00:16:05.360
Because we have a better covenant.

00:16:05.360 --> 00:16:06.709
His was with Abraham.

00:16:07.793 --> 00:16:11.040
He was just lining up with what his dad did, Abraham.

00:16:11.040 --> 00:16:14.079
And that was a great covenant still going on today.

00:16:14.079 --> 00:16:17.360
But we have a covenant, a better covenant, and it's with Jesus's blood.

00:16:19.409 --> 00:16:20.229
This week is Holy Week.

00:16:22.469 --> 00:16:27.371
Tomorrow is almost Easter or Good Friday or whatever is coming.

00:16:27.371 --> 00:16:28.880
And you know what?

00:16:28.880 --> 00:16:34.426
We're in a time of great thanksgiving, and great blessing is on our households.

00:16:34.426 --> 00:16:56.018
I believe that Jesus paid the price for every single one of you to not just walk in the blessing of finances, but to walk in health, wholeness, wellness, mental clarity—not a foggy mind, not a demonic mind, not torment in your sleep, not anything the devil has tried to throw at you.

00:16:56.018 --> 00:16:59.371
God is going to turn it around for good in your favor.

00:16:59.371 --> 00:17:05.846
I believe that what the devil meant for bad, God is going to turn it around for good.

00:17:05.846 --> 00:17:11.623
And you may turn around and go, 'Goodness and mercy, that's what you need to.

00:17:11.623 --> 00:17:12.137
' You turn around.

00:17:12.137 --> 00:17:12.800
That's what you're doing.

00:17:12.800 --> 00:17:20.605
You turn around, you're looking and you're saying, 'Goodness and mercy is following me, devil, all the days of my life, and I'm going to dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

00:17:20.605 --> 00:17:26.879
' So, you have taken your best shot, but I command sevenfold what you stole.

00:17:33.394 --> 00:17:34.857
And I believe in that same year right now a hundredfold return over the seeds I've sowed.

00:17:34.857 --> 00:17:42.000
I've given and I've sowed, and the Bible says, 'Whatsoever a man soweth, that will he also reap.

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:48.300
' Good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over will men give into your bosom.

00:17:50.340 --> 00:17:52.280
I believe that in famine my hands are going to prosper.

00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:55.120
So I don't care what the economy says.

